The race to replace former Mpumalanga ANC Chairperson David Mabuza is gaining momentum. The province has been without leadership since 2017 when Mabuza became the party’s deputy president. Violent clashes and court cases have plagued the party in its previous attempts to hold an elective conference. The ANC has since established an intervention task team to assist the province. Reporter Siphamandla Goge is in Mbombela in Mpumalanga with the latest. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 MBOMBELA - The race to replace former Mpumalanga ANC chairperson David Mabuza is gaining  momentum. The province has been without a leader since 2017 when Mabuza became the party’s deputy president. READ: Mpumalanga ANC revokes decision to reinstate PEC member charged with rape Violent clashes and court cases have plagued the party in its previous attempts to hold an elective conference. The ANC has since established an intervention task team to assist the province. Watch the video above for more details on this story